main event: Observers sighted two round objects heading straight down over Williams AFB, Arizona on June 30, 1947.
interesting points: The objects were reported to be light gray and traveling at a very high rate of speed., The conclusion leaned towards the objects being a meteor., The observation was ground-visual without physical evidence., There is an indication of a significant speed, as they were noted to move quickly in a straight line., The sighting occurred during a time when flying disc stories were prevalent in the media.
witness description: unknown, as no specific witnesses were recorded
